    println(
        """Выберите операцию: 
        |1. ДЗ 1-1
        |2. ДЗ 1-2
        |3. ДЗ 1-3
    """.trimMargin()
    )
    var userChoice: String? = readLine()
    userChoice = if (userChoice == "1") {
        commission()
    } else {
        return
    }
}
```

In this code, I removed the semicolon after the `if` statement's condition. I also removed the condition inside the parentheses of the `else` branch. Now, if `userChoice` is equal to "1", the `commission()` function will be invoked. Otherwise, the code will simply return from the `main()` function.

Please note that the code currently does not handle the case when `userChoice` is "2" or "3". You can add additional branches or logic to handle those cases as needed.

