If you want to print the chosen card at the end instead of immediately after the card choice, you can store the chosen card in a variable and print it later in the code. Here's the modified code:

```kotlin
fun commission() {
    val minimumRate: Int = 35
    val standardRate: Double = 0.0075

    println(
        """Выберите карту:
    | 1. Мир
    | 2. Visa
    | 3. Mastercard
""".trimMargin()
    )
    var cardChoice = readLine()?.toIntOrNull()
    var chosenCard: String? = null // Variable to store the chosen card

    if (cardChoice == 1) {
        chosenCard = "Мир"
    } else if (cardChoice == 2) {
        chosenCard = "Visa"
    } else if (cardChoice == 3) {
        chosenCard = "Mastercard"
    } else {
        println("Неправильный выбор!")
        return
    }

    println("Введите сумму: ")
    var amount = readLine()?.toDoubleOrNull()

    val commissionTotal = if (amount == null || amount <= 0) {
        println("Неправильная сумма.")
    } else if (amount <= minimumRate) {
        println("$minimumRate руб.")
    } else if (amount > minimumRate) {
        println("${amount * standardRate} руб. комиссия с  ")
    } else {
        println("Ошибка!")
    }

    // Print the chosen card at the end
    println("Выбранная карта: $chosenCard")
}
```

In this code, I added a variable called `chosenCard` to store the chosen card. Instead of printing the card immediately after the card choice, I assign the chosen card to the `chosenCard` variable based on the `cardChoice`. Then, at the end of the function, I print the chosen card using `println("Выбранная карта: $chosenCard")`.

Please note that if the `cardChoice` is not 1, 2, or 3, the `chosenCard` variable will remain `null`, and it will be printed as `null` at the end. You can handle this case by assigning a default value to `chosenCard` or modifying the logic as per your requirements.

