Yes, we can create a separate function to handle the printing of the messages and call it when needed. Here's an updated version of the `music` function with a separate `printMessage` function:

```kotlin
fun music() {
    println("Вы частый клиент? ")
    println("1. Да")
    println("2. Нет")
    var client: Int? = readLine()?.toIntOrNull()

    println("Сколько хотите потратить на музыку: ")
    var moneySpent: Int? = readLine()?.toInt()

    if (moneySpent == null || moneySpent <= 0) {
        println("Ничего не потратили.")
    } else if (moneySpent > 0 && moneySpent < NO_DISCOUNT) {
        printMessage("У Вас нет скидки", "Сумма к оплате: $moneySpent")
    } else if (moneySpent >= NO_DISCOUNT && moneySpent < FIRST_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = moneySpent - onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()) // Additional 1% discount for frequent customers
        }
        printMessage("Ваша скидка - 1%!", "Она составит: ${onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())}", "Сумма к оплате: $discount")
    } else if (moneySpent >= FIRST_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = fivePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()) // Additional 1% discount for frequent customers
        }
        var toPay: Double = moneySpent - discount
        printMessage("Ваша скидка - 5%!", "Она составит: $discount", "Сумма к оплате: $toPay")
    }
}

fun printMessage(vararg messages: String) {
    for (message in messages) {
        println(message)
    }
}
```

In this updated code, I have created a new function called `printMessage` that takes a variable number of `String` arguments. It iterates over the `messages` array and prints each message using the `println` function. The `printMessage` function is then called with the appropriate messages in each branch of the `if` statement.

This approach helps to make the code more modular and reusable by separating the printing logic into a separate function.

