Why does this give me an error:
        } else (amount <= 0) {
            println("Неправильная сумма.")
        }

The error occurs because the `else` statement in your code is not properly structured. The `else` statement should not have a condition within parentheses. Instead, it should be a simple `else` block without any condition.

To fix the error, you can modify the code as follows:

```kotlin
fun main() {
    val minimumRate: Int = 35
    val standardRate: Double = 0.0075

    println("Введите сумму: ")
    var amount = readLine()?.toDoubleOrNull()

    while (amount != null && amount >= 0) {
        val commissionTotal = if (amount <= minimumRate) {
            println("$minimumRate руб.")
        } else if (amount > minimumRate) {
            println("${amount * standardRate} руб.")
        } else {
            println("Неправильная сумма.")
        }

        println("Введите сумму: ")
        amount = readLine()?.toDoubleOrNull()
    }

    println("Неправильная сумма.")
}
```

In this modified code, I removed the condition `(amount <= 0)` from the `else` statement and replaced it with a simple `else` block. Now, when the `amount` is neither less than or equal to the minimum rate nor greater than the minimum rate, it will execute the `else` block and print the message "Неправильная сумма."

Please note that the `else` block will only be executed if the `amount` is exactly equal to zero. If you want to handle negative amounts as well, you can modify the condition in the `while` loop to `amount != null && amount > 0`.

