The error "Unexpected tokens (use ';' to separate expressions on the same line)" occurs when there are multiple expressions on the same line without using the semicolon `;` to separate them. To fix this error, you need to add semicolons to separate the expressions.

In your code, the error is occurring in the line where you subtract the 1% discount from the `discount` variable. To fix it, you can add a semicolon after the subtraction operation. Here's the updated code:

```kotlin
fun music() {
    println("Вы частый клиент? ")
    println("1. Да")
    println("2. Нет")
    var client: Int? = readLine()?.toIntOrNull()

    println("Сколько хотите потратить на музыку: ")
    var moneySpent: Int? = readLine()?.toInt()

    if (moneySpent == null || moneySpent <= 0) {
        println("Ничего не потратили.")
    } else if (moneySpent > 0 && moneySpent < NO_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = moneySpent - onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()); // Add semicolon here
        }
        println("Ваша скидка - 1%!")
        println("Она составит: ${onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())}")
        println("Сумма к оплате: $discount")
    } else if (moneySpent >= NO_DISCOUNT && moneySpent < FIRST_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = moneySpent - onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()); // Add semicolon here
        }
        println("Ваша скидка - 1%!")
        println("Она составит: ${onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())}")
        println("Сумма к оплате: $discount")
    } else if (moneySpent >= FIRST_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = fivePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()); // Add semicolon here
        }
        var toPay: Double = moneySpent - discount
        println("Ваша скидка - 5%!")
        println("Она составит: $discount")
        println("Сумма к оплате: $toPay")
    }
}
```

By adding semicolons after the subtraction operations, the error should be resolved. Let me know if you have any further questions!

