To add an additional 1% discount for customers who say they are frequent customers, you can modify the `music` function as follows:

```kotlin
fun music() {
    println("Вы частый клиент? ")
    println("1. Да")
    println("2. Нет")
    var client: Int? = readLine()?.toIntOrNull()

    println("Сколько хотите потратить на музыку: ")
    var moneySpent: Int? = readLine()?.toInt()

    if (moneySpent == null || moneySpent <= 0) {
        println("Ничего не потратили.")
    } else if (moneySpent > 0 && moneySpent < NO_DISCOUNT) {
        println("У Вас нет скидки")
        println("Сумма к оплате: $moneySpent")
    } else if (moneySpent >= NO_DISCOUNT && moneySpent < FIRST_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = moneySpent - onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()) // Additional 1% discount for frequent customers
        }
        println("Ваша скидка - 1%!")
        println("Она составит: ${onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())}")
        println("Сумма к оплате: $discount")
    } else if (moneySpent >= FIRST_DISCOUNT) {
        var discount: Double = fivePercent(moneySpent.toDouble())
        if (client == 1) {
            discount -= onePercent(moneySpent.toDouble()) // Additional 1% discount for frequent customers
        }
        var toPay: Double = moneySpent - discount
        println("Ваша скидка - 5%!")
        println("Она составит: $discount")
        println("Сумма к оплате: $toPay")
    }
}
```

In this updated code, I have added an additional check inside the `if (moneySpent >= NO_DISCOUNT && moneySpent < FIRST_DISCOUNT)` and `if (moneySpent >= FIRST_DISCOUNT)` blocks to subtract an additional 1% discount from the `discount` variable if the `client` variable is equal to 1 (indicating that the customer is a frequent customer).

Please note that the `fivePercentClient` function is not used in the provided code, so I have not made any changes to it. If you intend to use it, you may need to modify it accordingly.

