To fix the error "Expecting an element," you need to provide an element or statement after the `else if` condition. In your code, the `else if` condition `println("Понравилось $input человек")` is missing the required element or statement. 

If you want to print the message "Понравилось $input человек" when the condition is true, you can modify the code as follows:

```kotlin
fun Likes() {
    println("Введите количество лайков: ")
    val input: Int? = readLine()?.toIntOrNull()

    if (input == 0) {
        println("Никому пока не понравилось")
    } else if (input == 1) {
        println("Понравилось 1 человеку")
    } else if (input != null) {
        println("Понравилось $input человек")
    }
}
```

In this updated code, we added an additional `else if` condition `input != null` to handle cases where the input is not 0 or 1. Now, if the input is 0, the message "Никому пока не понравилось" will be printed. If the input is 1, the message "Понравилось 1 человеку" will be printed. For any other non-null input, the message "Понравилось $input человек" will be printed.

